1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,240
ALL DEPICTED EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,280
Duang.

3
00:00:18,840 --> 00:00:20,040
- Gam?
- Hi.

4
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:21,120
<i>You're single, right?</i>

5
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:23,160
- Hey!
- Back off.

6
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:24,720
Are you all right?

7
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,760
I simply don't like it
when I can't control my emotions.

8
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:30,880
I'm prepared to love you
with everything I have.

9
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:36,760
Why are you taking me back to your place?
Got something planned?

10
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:38,800
Don't do this to me.

11
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:41,480
I could literally die.

12
00:00:44,040 --> 00:00:46,840
You haven't even won me over.
Are you really dying?

13
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,600
I'd better hurry then.

14
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,760
You think you're really funny, huh?

15
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:15,880
I don't joke when it comes to you.

16
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:20,040
I'm serious too. What's it going to be?

17
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:24,040
You really want me to help you shower?

18
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:28,440
Why the hell did you ask
if you thought I wouldn't let you?

19
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:31,680
Well…

20
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:34,720
See? I got you now.

21
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,480
You were just pulling my leg.

22
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:38,280
Hey, I mean…

23
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:41,480
Let me explain myself.
I didn't expect you to let me.

24
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:45,320
Then remember this. Never pull my leg.

25
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:50,600
Well…

26
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,640
Shall we take a shower?

27
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:54,120
You missed your chance.

28
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:10,320
Next time, I won't fail!

29
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:12,720
Next time, just you wait!

30
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:38,800
Hey.

31
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,720
I'm putting it here, okay?

32
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:44,360
Come sleep. I have a game tomorrow.

33
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:48,280
You're right.
You're up against the Logistics guys.

34
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:50,880
I'm sure you're going to smash them.

35
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:53,280
That's because I'll be cheering for you!

36
00:03:58,080 --> 00:03:58,920
See?

37
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,040
We each got a tattoo.

38
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,560
This feels like a dream.

39
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:08,320
Thank you.

40
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,080
You sleep there.

41
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:17,240
Don't cross the line.

42
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:18,800
Understand?

43
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:22,600
Do you understand?

44
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,240
Yes, I do.

45
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:32,800
I'm delighted to be
sharing this bed with you again.

46
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,960
It feels like I'm being attacked by you.

47
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:38,240
My heart, I mean. It's totally gone!

48
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:41,320
- Dead already?
- Not really.

49
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:43,280
You're melting my heart.

50
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:47,040
I feel like melted chocolate.

51
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,600
Sweet dreams.

52
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,240
No, I must not cross the line.

53
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:05,920
But staying on top of the line
should be fine, right?

54
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:15,480
Once I'm done with class,
I'll rush there to support you.

55
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:21,440
Promise me that
you won't get yourself hurt.

56
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:31,920
Promise?

57
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:35,160
Promise me first.

58
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:38,120
I promise you.

59
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:47,120
I won't get hurt.

60
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:52,200
You've promised!

61
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:54,360
Is there anything you want?
I'll get it for you.

62
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,400
No.

63
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,040
Having you there is enough.

64
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:06,560
Come give me a big hug!

65
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,640
I'll be there to cheer you on!

66
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:24,400
"Having you there is enough."

67
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:27,040
"Having you there is enough!"

68
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,080
Where should we sit?

69
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,520
Is Qin here?

70
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,160
Do you see him?

71
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:18,760
No, I don't.

72
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:21,040
Gosh, you're so uniquely stupid.

73
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:23,840
If you're in such a rush,
why didn't you come yesterday?

74
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:24,960
All right.

75
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:27,760
If I could've booked a seat,
I'd have been here since yesterday.

76
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:30,760
When will Duang stop being madly in love?

77
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:33,040
After the end of the world, I bet.

78
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,000
Ready?

79
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:49,360
Three! Four!

80
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:51,240
Ready!

81
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,640
There are cheerleaders too?

82
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:55,960
Three and four!

83
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,680
Qin, you've got this!

84
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:59,480
Qin, you're fantastic!

85
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:01,080
Qin, you slay!

86
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,120
Qin…

87
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:04,120
You're so cute!

88
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:09,800
Gosh!

89
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:14,160
Is that all you've got, girls?

90
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:17,080
You can't be cheering for Qin like we do.

91
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,640
Just watch us.

92
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,480
Get ready!

93
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:22,800
So ready!

94
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:27,080
Three! Four! Bang!

95
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:29,760
On fire!

96
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,360
- Slay!
- Slay!

97
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,600
Slay!

98
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:34,679
- Slay, king!
- Slay, king!

99
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,679
Bet you can't top that.

100
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:38,600
Duang.

101
00:08:38,679 --> 00:08:40,960
Don't let them win.
Give it your best shot!

102
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:43,039
I have to give it to them.

103
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:45,840
The match is starting soon.

104
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:49,760
Athletes, please stand by
on the sidelines.

105
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:02,920
There he is! Qin is here!

106
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,440
Yeah! I know!

107
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,640
Qin!

108
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:13,960
Qin!

109
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,680
Hey, Qin.

110
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:28,520
Qin! You've got this!

111
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:33,960
You might as well
bring a telescope at this rate.

112
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:39,640
If both teams are ready,
please get on the court.

113
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,400
Ready? Go.

114
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,320
Let's go. They're calling.

115
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:51,120
Today's match is between

116
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:54,000
the blue team
from the Faculty of Logistics

117
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:58,240
and their opponent,
the red team from the College of Music.

118
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:09,400
Let's have a good, clean game.

119
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:11,840
Embrace the spirit of good sportsmanship

120
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:16,320
to foster friendship
among fellow students.

121
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,120
Qin!

122
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,320
Qin, you've got this!

123
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,880
I'm right here!

124
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,200
Qin, show them what you're made of!

125
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:29,400
There.

126
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,240
It's these two.

127
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:46,080
The crowds from the College of Music
seem very lively.

128
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:57,600
Red wins the tip-off
and gets possession of the ball.

129
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:05,240
Red is passing the ball nicely,

130
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:07,440
and it finally ends up with No. 7,

131
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:11,920
who goes in for a layup
and scores the first two-pointer.

132
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:17,760
Let's now look at
the counterattack from blue.

133
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:20,280
With this clear space,
No. 7 is jumping at the gap.

134
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:22,480
There's our three-pointer! Bang!

135
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:23,760
That's not gonna work.

136
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:24,920
Blue won't back down,

137
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:28,080
bouncing back
with a three-pointer from No. 7.

138
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:35,600
Red makes it a tight game
with a two-pointer!

139
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:40,320
However, blue responds
instantly with a shot

140
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:42,120
that catches red off guard.

141
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:44,000
Man, what the hell?

142
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:46,200
No. 21 from blue
tries to take a shot, but misses.

143
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:48,480
The ball falls into the hands of No. 7,

144
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:50,280
who makes a hook shot!

145
00:11:51,480 --> 00:11:53,960
There goes the whistle,

146
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:56,920
concluding the first quarter 20-24.

147
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,920
Blue is ahead by four points.

148
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:03,120
Let's see what plan red has
to bounce back.

149
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:06,360
Play defensively
and conserve your energy for now, okay?

150
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:09,400
As for you,
move fast and hold the center line.

151
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:11,840
Push slowly, let Qin do the attack.

152
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:14,640
Get the ball and pass.
You two, score at opposite ends.

153
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:19,480
Let's move on to the second quarter
with red making the first move.

154
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:24,480
No. 23 goes up for a shot.

155
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:26,560
There it goes, a two-pointer!

156
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:37,280
The momentum swings back
in red's favor after No. 23 scores.

157
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:42,800
With red's game plan,
Blue is like deer in the headlights.

158
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:46,040
Gotta give it up for red's offense,
especially from No. 23.

159
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:48,800
He shoots,
he passes the ball, you name it.

160
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:52,320
Looks like red has got the game
in the palm of their hands.

161
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:54,720
They're the only ones
scoring at this moment.

162
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,280
That concludes the second quarter.

163
00:12:56,360 --> 00:13:00,000
Red has turned the game around.
They're now in the lead by eight points!

164
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:03,000
Understood? Be aggressive and play strong.

165
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,480
Don't be afraid of them.

166
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:06,880
All right. This is now the third quarter.

167
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:09,200
Let's see how this game plays out.

168
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:17,440
Blue is getting physical and scores.

169
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:26,920
No. 7 continues aggressively,

170
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:29,920
pushing his way inside
and scoring once again.

171
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:33,840
It seems like blue is shifting
their game plan in the third quarter

172
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:37,200
to be more physical.

173
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:41,120
Here comes
another scoring opportunity for blue.

174
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:45,160
One push, and it's a layup.
It's a two-pointer!

175
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:50,040
Blue's supporters
are certainly in a great mood.

176
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:56,480
Red, however, is not to be outdone.
They're still at it.

177
00:13:56,560 --> 00:14:00,320
The third quarter has been neck and neck.

178
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:06,560
That's it for the third quarter.

179
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,120
Relax. Same strategy.

180
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:11,120
If you can't,
have PK help you advance the ball.

181
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:13,560
Take the ball from them and score.

182
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:15,760
Our game plan is fast-paced,
so we can do this.

183
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:18,280
- Logistics!
- Come on, let's go for another quarter.

184
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:20,920
One, two, three, Rhythm.

185
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:28,080
We're in the fourth quarter,
the final stretch.

186
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:29,880
It's anyone's game at this point.

187
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:38,920
Gotta say, the scores are close.

188
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:41,200
This is anyone's game.

189
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,880
No. 23 makes his way in,

190
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:49,120
goes up for the layup and scores!

191
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:51,440
What a beautiful shot.

192
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:54,160
No. 7 from red fakes perfectly and scores.

193
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:55,960
And No. 7 from the other team…

194
00:14:58,320 --> 00:15:00,680
Things are quite heated!

195
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:04,440
Right now,
both teams keep trading the lead.

196
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:10,160
We've got a nail-biter here.

197
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:12,840
No telling what'll happen next.

198
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:18,080
Qin!

199
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:32,000
It seems like one of the players
may be injured.

200
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,440
It's all part of the game.

201
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,720
However, blue doesn't care
in this final stretch.

202
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,320
They're immediately retaliating.

203
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,160
Hey!

204
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:47,240
Less than a minute remains.

205
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:49,320
Every point counts.

206
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:52,400
Blue fakes a pass and shoots!

207
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:54,760
That's a three-pointer!

208
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:57,640
Blue is now in the lead,

209
00:15:57,720 --> 00:15:59,800
which puts red in real trouble.

210
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:02,200
It's the final chance for red to score.

211
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:05,080
No. 23 takes possession of the ball.

212
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:09,680
Keep going!
Give it a spin and take a leap!

213
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:20,600
- Hey!
- That's a shooting foul.

214
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:23,400
That was a dangerous play,
considering how aggressive it was.

215
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:26,560
You could call it unsportsmanlike.

216
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:27,520
Qin!

217
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:30,440
So fucking aggressive!

218
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:32,120
Can't you just play fair?

219
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,400
Yeah!

220
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:34,480
Come on! Ref!

221
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:36,040
Ref!

222
00:16:37,880 --> 00:16:38,760
Two shots.

223
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:43,760
Of course, red will get two free throws.

224
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:55,440
Right now, there's only
23 seconds left on the clock.

225
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:58,200
If red can score
two free throws back-to-back,

226
00:16:58,280 --> 00:17:00,600
there will be no hope blue.

227
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:02,360
- Miss!
- Score!

228
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:19,680
Both teams are now tied at 61.

229
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:23,560
If red scores again,
it'll be a big advantage for them.

230
00:17:23,640 --> 00:17:24,880
If they don't,

231
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:30,520
this will give blue a chance
to respond with their final play.

232
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,200
That was incredible!

233
00:18:56,280 --> 00:19:00,920
The match ends with a three-pointer
from red's No. 23!

234
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:06,760
He seals the win
with a final score of 64-61.

235
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:25,320
Damn. Even though we didn't win,

236
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:26,640
that asshole got hurt.

237
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:28,400
- So satisfying.
- Yeah.

238
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:29,560
I knocked him down.

239
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:30,800
- I saw that.
- Sheesh.

240
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:40,240
- Hey!
- Hey!

241
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:42,000
Duang!

242
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:43,560
- Duang!
- Hey!

243
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,960
What the fuck, man?

244
00:19:50,680 --> 00:19:52,640
He's got his guardian angel.

245
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:57,400
Right. Bastard!

246
00:19:57,480 --> 00:19:58,320
- Hey!
- Duang!

247
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:00,400
Bring it.

248
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,480
Let him go and come with me.

249
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:06,240
Listen to him.

250
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:11,600
- Duang!
- Hey!

251
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:22,600
Sheesh. Taking care of each other?

252
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:24,440
- Limping away?
- Let's just go.

253
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:28,200
Sorry, boys.

254
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:29,880
Coming through.

255
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:31,400
Excuse us.

256
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:32,680
Make way for us, please.

257
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:46,840
- Go on without me.
- All right, fine.

258
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:48,320
Duang, take care of Qin, okay?

259
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:50,240
Let's go, guys.

260
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:52,520
See you.

261
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:24,360
Why did you do that?

262
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:29,840
You told me you wouldn't get hurt.

263
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:36,120
I already did. It already happened.

264
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,440
There's nothing either of us could do.

265
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:40,040
Why is it that only you got hurt?

266
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:41,240
Duang.

267
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,080
Get a grip.

268
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:49,560
How can I not worry?

269
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:54,840
I'm as hurt as you are.

270
00:21:56,840 --> 00:21:58,280
It's even worse for me.

271
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:07,400
How is that even possible?

272
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:55,960
I'm sorry.

273
00:22:58,160 --> 00:23:01,520
It was my fault
I couldn't keep my promise.

274
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:22,160
I told you I wouldn't get hurt…

275
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:25,200
but I did.

276
00:23:28,360 --> 00:23:29,440
Qin.

277
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:32,760
I'm sorry.

278
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:35,840
Forgive me.

279
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:41,200
I'm sorry too.

280
00:23:45,080 --> 00:23:46,360
Thank you…

281
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:49,680
for taking such good care of me.

282
00:24:32,720 --> 00:24:33,640
See?

283
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:37,080
I told you not to move too much.

284
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:39,360
You're scolding me for this?

285
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:40,960
You're as fierce as a dog.

286
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,960
It could get worse, okay?

287
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:50,240
Are you still mad?

288
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:53,200
I'm not mad at you,

289
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:55,920
but at that guy who hurt you.

290
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:00,120
I'm sorry.

291
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,880
I'm sorry.

292
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,360
I'm sorry.

293
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:05,680
Stop with that voice.

294
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:08,880
You've already got my heart.

295
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:12,800
This time, I'm going to die for real.

296
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:16,120
You forgive me too easily.

297
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:18,680
You know me too well.

298
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:24,960
Well…

299
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:32,240
What did you just say?

300
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:34,600
I'm hungry.

301
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:38,040
I'm hungry right now.

302
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:39,600
Come on!

303
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:42,400
My heart almost sank.

304
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:45,120
I thought you said something else.

305
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:48,960
In this economy,

306
00:25:49,040 --> 00:25:52,680
nothing beats
two packs of rice for ten baht.

307
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:56,160
Check this out. It's stir-fried
whiteleg shrimp with garlic.

308
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:59,000
It's rare to find this dish at this price.

309
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:01,040
Am I going to die if I eat this?

310
00:26:03,080 --> 00:26:06,160
Don't be so pessimistic, all right?

311
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:08,360
This is who I am.

312
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:11,200
I'm good at cooking, you know?

313
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:15,600
Here.

314
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:18,800
All done. Eat up if you can.

315
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:21,760
If not, throw it away!

316
00:26:29,560 --> 00:26:30,680
Nom, nom.

317
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:35,880
You're spoiling me. No need to feed me.

318
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:37,760
My hands are fine.

319
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:39,000
It's my ankle.

320
00:26:40,560 --> 00:26:42,560
I want to take care of you.

321
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:45,160
I want you to get plenty of rest,

322
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:48,000
eat your favorite foods,
and do whatever you want.

323
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:50,760
What's that got to do with anything?

324
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:52,720
It's with this!

325
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:57,760
All that talk, same old meaning.

326
00:26:58,640 --> 00:26:59,840
Come on now.

327
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,480
Whatever. Here.

328
00:27:01,560 --> 00:27:04,600
Qin, nom, nom. Qin, you're a good boy.

329
00:27:04,680 --> 00:27:06,280
Good boy, nom, nom.

330
00:27:06,360 --> 00:27:08,200
Nom, nom, good job!

331
00:27:16,560 --> 00:27:17,920
It's as simple as that.

332
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:20,480
All I have is you.

333
00:27:20,560 --> 00:27:22,600
Spoiling you this much
means nothing to me.

334
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:31,920
Can you do me a favor?

335
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:35,040
Do tell.

336
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:37,680
I want to practice dance.

337
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:40,960
I've dedicated
too much time to basketball.

338
00:27:41,520 --> 00:27:43,400
But your foot is hurt.

339
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:45,360
Forget about that.

340
00:27:46,480 --> 00:27:48,640
Another big event
is just around the corner.

341
00:27:48,720 --> 00:27:50,840
Hey! You're right!

342
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:52,320
We've only got a few days left!

343
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:57,160
What do we do?

344
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:22,120
Looking for someone?

345
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:26,600
Come on. You already know.

346
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:29,840
You're hooked?
You rarely go for the same person.

347
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:33,480
Everything happens for a reason.

348
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:38,480
If you think this is your moment,
it'll always be yours.

349
00:28:40,200 --> 00:28:41,920
You sound like a fortune teller.

350
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:43,920
You believe in them?

351
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:46,840
Crazy. Who would?

352
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:49,920
I don't really mind if I get rejected.

353
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:57,320
I do believe things happen for a reason.

354
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,800
Then tonight is my moment.

355
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:38,360
And…

356
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:44,920
You're only here to compliment me?

357
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,360
What should I do?

358
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:53,840
I'm not the type to say one thing
and mean another.

359
00:30:22,360 --> 00:30:23,400
Bottoms up.

360
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:40,120
Fantastic.

361
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:48,240
I heard you got hurt.

362
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:50,080
Can you still dance?

363
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:58,040
Are you pretending
because you're afraid you'll lose?

364
00:32:58,120 --> 00:33:00,760
I usually don't like competition.

365
00:33:01,320 --> 00:33:04,000
But with you guys, why should we give up?

366
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:24,960
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

367
00:33:35,520 --> 00:33:37,040
Okay.

368
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:40,360
From what I've seen,
things have gone pretty well.

369
00:33:40,440 --> 00:33:43,240
It's just that your accents
need a bit more work.

370
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:03,520
How are you doing, Qin?
Will your ankle heal in time?

371
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:07,920
<i>It will. The pain is mostly gone.</i>

372
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:10,639
Does it hurt?

373
00:34:10,719 --> 00:34:13,600
I want to take the pain for you.

374
00:34:13,679 --> 00:34:14,840
Ridiculous.

375
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:21,600
<i>That's great.</i>

376
00:34:21,679 --> 00:34:25,600
I'm not worried about your dancing.
You'd better heal up in time.

377
00:34:25,679 --> 00:34:29,040
I'd like to add something.

378
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:32,040
For your singing technique,

379
00:34:32,120 --> 00:34:35,800
you've already nailed it, and
I'm not worried about that.

380
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:40,880
But the emotion isn't coming through yet.

381
00:34:42,239 --> 00:34:43,120
I'm sorry?

382
00:34:44,040 --> 00:34:49,199
I'm not sure about it myself,
as I'm not an expert.

383
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:50,400
How about this?

384
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:54,360
Look at how professional singers
convey their emotions.

385
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:55,960
Learn from them and adapt it, okay?

386
00:34:56,040 --> 00:34:57,840
I'll sing this first part.

387
00:34:57,920 --> 00:35:00,200
And I'll follow it up with this.

388
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:26,720
One more time?

389
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:17,000
<i>Hey.</i>

390
00:36:19,720 --> 00:36:22,680
MY STUPID-ASS BRO

391
00:36:24,440 --> 00:36:25,440
<i>Hello, Funan?</i>

392
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:30,240
Right. Mom says she misses you.

393
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:33,200
<i>You rarely reply to the family group chat.</i>

394
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:38,280
Tell her that I also miss her,
but the opening is soon.

395
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:41,040
Your dance performance? When is it?

396
00:36:43,640 --> 00:36:44,640
Why do you need to know?

397
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:48,000
What? I'll be there to see you.

398
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:51,000
<i>Why? Afraid your friends will tease you?</i>

399
00:36:51,080 --> 00:36:52,560
My friends might,

400
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:56,400
but my rivals definitely will.

401
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:58,720
Come on. What's there to be afraid of?

402
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:00,400
You're such a chicken.

403
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:01,640
Gosh, Funan.

404
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:05,080
Don't come then.
I'll have my friend send you a video.

405
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:07,280
Are you gonna tell me?

406
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:09,520
You won't be at work?

407
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:11,040
I've been feeling lazy lately.

408
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:13,640
<i>I'll be there, okay?</i>

409
00:37:13,720 --> 00:37:17,080
Fine. Come if you want.

410
00:37:17,160 --> 00:37:19,000
But don't tell Mom and Dad, okay?

411
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:21,680
<i>The run-through is tomorrow.</i>
<i>The opening is the day after.</i>

412
00:37:23,120 --> 00:37:24,880
Bye, Funan.

413
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:36,720
Hey!

414
00:37:36,800 --> 00:37:38,080
- You like this song?
<i>- Today…</i>

415
00:37:38,160 --> 00:37:39,280
It's also my favorite.

416
00:37:39,360 --> 00:37:41,040
<i>There's a new song I just wrote.</i>

417
00:37:41,120 --> 00:37:42,240
It's got great vibes.

418
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:44,320
<i>And I'd like you all to hear it.</i>

419
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:47,480
<i>I hope you like it.</i>

420
00:38:05,240 --> 00:38:11,600
<i>Do you think I'm good enough for you?</i>

421
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:18,680
<i>Do I look like someone from your dreams?</i>

422
00:38:20,920 --> 00:38:26,520
<i>If you knew something about me</i>

423
00:38:27,240 --> 00:38:30,960
<i>And saw something</i>

424
00:38:31,040 --> 00:38:35,120
<i>I wonder how disappointed you'd be</i>

425
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:40,960
<i>I want you to know that</i>
<i>No matter how things change</i>

426
00:38:43,760 --> 00:38:49,560
<i>My heart will always remain the same</i>

427
00:38:50,360 --> 00:38:54,320
<i>Would you still love me?</i>

428
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:59,040
<i>Could you accept me for who I am?</i>

429
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:05,120
<i>If I were just a nobody</i>
<i>Who couldn't live up to your dreams?</i>

430
00:39:05,840 --> 00:39:09,520
<i>Could you still love me?</i>

431
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:14,440
<i>Would I be the one you want</i>

432
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:20,320
<i>If all I have is a heart that wants you?</i>

433
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:24,920
<i>Can you love me for my heart?</i>

434
00:39:40,800 --> 00:39:41,920
I'm hungry.

435
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:47,120
Actually, I just ordered KFC.

436
00:39:47,200 --> 00:39:49,480
It should arrive soon. Sit tight, okay?

437
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:01,960
- Here it is.
- Give it here.

438
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:05,840
No way. I'll unpack it for you.
Go wash your hands.

439
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:06,920
I'll unpack it myself.

440
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:45,920
Slowly.

441
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:48,280
You enjoy Wingz Zabb this much?

442
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:50,680
I do.

443
00:40:51,880 --> 00:40:53,360
What about you? Do you?

444
00:40:54,640 --> 00:40:55,480
It's all right.

445
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:57,800
And…

446
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:04,040
Between Wingz Zabb and me,

447
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:05,360
which do you prefer?

448
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:10,080
I prefer

449
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:12,200
Wingz Zabb.

450
00:41:16,280 --> 00:41:18,160
I'm just as spicy, you know?

451
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:29,600
Watch it. You're making a mess.

452
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:32,720
How exactly?

453
00:41:33,440 --> 00:41:34,280
This?

454
00:41:53,960 --> 00:41:55,160
Hey.

455
00:41:55,240 --> 00:41:57,680
Tinn asked us to fill out the form again.

456
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:01,240
A team name is required.

457
00:42:02,800 --> 00:42:03,720
Think of one.

458
00:42:03,800 --> 00:42:05,320
You have better taste than I do.

459
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:07,640
All I can think of are cringey names

460
00:42:07,720 --> 00:42:10,720
like "GodLike007," "Sigmaboys,"
and stuff like that.

461
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:13,160
I'm not the only one on this team.

462
00:42:15,320 --> 00:42:16,520
We'll think of one together.

463
00:42:22,080 --> 00:42:25,760
How about this team name?

464
00:42:27,080 --> 00:42:28,200
How about "Duang & Qin"?

465
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:30,120
No.

466
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:32,680
I want a name that is

467
00:42:32,760 --> 00:42:35,520
unique, just like you.

468
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:37,760
What?

469
00:42:38,600 --> 00:42:40,840
I was taken aback when you said that.

470
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:42,920
Are you referring to what Pae said?

471
00:42:43,560 --> 00:42:44,640
What do you mean?

472
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:47,320
Nothing.

473
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:49,680
Well…

474
00:42:55,800 --> 00:42:56,680
Here.

475
00:42:56,760 --> 00:42:57,880
This.

476
00:42:58,400 --> 00:43:00,320
It hurts less to say it myself.

477
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:05,560
You still think you're not the best?

478
00:43:08,760 --> 00:43:10,760
That's what everyone around me says.

479
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:14,120
It's also based on the name of a song.

480
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:36,240
Are you trying to make me feel better?

481
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:37,880
I'm not.

482
00:43:38,360 --> 00:43:39,800
I just want you to know that

483
00:43:40,520 --> 00:43:42,800
even though you think that
you're not the best,

484
00:43:43,560 --> 00:43:44,800
you're good in your own way.

485
00:43:51,120 --> 00:43:53,080
That really opened something up inside me.

486
00:43:54,840 --> 00:43:55,840
Finish the food already.

487
00:44:30,240 --> 00:44:32,640
Okay. Attention, guys.

488
00:44:32,720 --> 00:44:36,560
We're doing the run-through
from start to finish.

489
00:44:36,640 --> 00:44:38,600
Let's start with the cues.

490
00:44:38,680 --> 00:44:41,320
Sol and Peem are going first.

491
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:43,000
After that, it's Duang and Qin's.

492
00:44:43,080 --> 00:44:44,520
Then Alice will do an improv,

493
00:44:44,600 --> 00:44:46,960
followed by the dance club. Okay?

494
00:44:48,320 --> 00:44:51,600
If there are no questions,
let's start the run-through.

495
00:44:56,240 --> 00:44:57,480
Are you okay?

496
00:44:59,360 --> 00:45:00,880
I thought I'd be fine,

497
00:45:00,960 --> 00:45:02,800
but I don't think I am.

498
00:45:03,560 --> 00:45:05,200
I'm going crazy.

499
00:45:05,680 --> 00:45:07,000
It's okay. Take it easy.

500
00:45:07,560 --> 00:45:08,880
Take deep breaths.

501
00:45:22,200 --> 00:45:24,040
All right. Let's do this.

502
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:03,640
Hey.

503
00:46:04,200 --> 00:46:05,480
Shaking in your boots?

504
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:08,320
Stop caring about them.

505
00:46:46,640 --> 00:46:48,520
When I went onstage,

506
00:46:49,840 --> 00:46:51,680
my mind immediately went blank.

507
00:46:52,720 --> 00:46:54,760
I can imagine how well I'll do tomorrow.

508
00:46:59,440 --> 00:47:01,400
Worrying gets you nowhere.

509
00:47:05,800 --> 00:47:07,080
And…

510
00:47:10,280 --> 00:47:12,160
If I mess this up…

511
00:47:13,720 --> 00:47:15,200
how would that make you feel?

512
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:17,920
Will you be mad at me?

513
00:47:20,800 --> 00:47:21,800
No.

514
00:47:23,280 --> 00:47:24,720
Why would I be mad at you?

515
00:47:26,760 --> 00:47:29,400
I believe you'll do your best
in your own way.

516
00:47:32,920 --> 00:47:34,360
If you really tried your best,

517
00:47:35,480 --> 00:47:37,080
messing up…

518
00:47:39,240 --> 00:47:41,240
doesn't mean you didn't care.

519
00:47:46,520 --> 00:47:49,840
I'll try even harder.

520
00:47:51,240 --> 00:47:52,200
No need.

521
00:47:53,840 --> 00:47:55,520
No need to push it any further.

522
00:47:58,200 --> 00:47:59,520
Because you've got this.

523
00:48:04,160 --> 00:48:05,640
Let's just say,

524
00:48:05,720 --> 00:48:08,600
if you fuck up and
embarrass yourself in front of everyone,

525
00:48:08,680 --> 00:48:10,680
I'll stay on the sinking ship with you.

526
00:48:11,760 --> 00:48:14,400
We'll fuck up together. Okay?

527
00:48:23,960 --> 00:48:25,480
I know that you're smiling.

528
00:48:27,800 --> 00:48:28,800
I don't know.

529
00:48:32,640 --> 00:48:35,120
I'm happy you're by my side.

530
00:48:36,520 --> 00:48:37,920
Where else can I go?

531
00:48:42,080 --> 00:48:43,520
I'm so lucky that

532
00:48:44,840 --> 00:48:46,680
I've been giving it my all
just to love you.

533
00:48:46,760 --> 00:48:48,400
So fucking corny.

534
00:48:55,960 --> 00:48:58,560
Yet someone's ears always turn red.

535
00:48:59,880 --> 00:49:02,880
I'm just nervous
about the performance tomorrow.

536
00:49:09,400 --> 00:49:10,640
What are you looking at?

537
00:49:20,600 --> 00:49:21,480
There you go.

538
00:49:21,560 --> 00:49:22,560
Perfect spot.

539
00:49:22,640 --> 00:49:25,480
I can see Qin and Duang
very clearly from here.

540
00:49:25,560 --> 00:49:27,600
We're not going to block others, are we?

541
00:49:28,600 --> 00:49:31,040
Block others? Who?
I don't care. I wanna see my friends.

542
00:49:33,960 --> 00:49:36,520
POL ALICE
WE LOVE YOU!

543
00:49:39,240 --> 00:49:40,160
Oops.

544
00:49:43,600 --> 00:49:44,560
What's wrong with you?

545
00:49:44,640 --> 00:49:45,720
Who stepped on your toes?

546
00:49:45,800 --> 00:49:47,320
Stepped on your face, more like.

547
00:49:47,400 --> 00:49:48,520
I was practicing.

548
00:49:48,600 --> 00:49:50,280
I was warming my voice up.

549
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:52,080
My throat's dying up.

550
00:49:52,560 --> 00:49:53,880
Were you letting the notes out?

551
00:49:53,960 --> 00:49:55,960
Of course, I'm the lead vocalist.

552
00:49:56,520 --> 00:49:58,600
Good. We can help you cheer.

553
00:49:59,440 --> 00:50:01,640
Yeah!

554
00:50:02,120 --> 00:50:04,840
Look at him.
He's cheering on everyone's behalf.

555
00:50:17,280 --> 00:50:18,240
Hello, everyone.

556
00:50:18,320 --> 00:50:22,640
Welcome to this year's showcase.

557
00:50:22,720 --> 00:50:25,200
How is everyone doing? Are you excited?

558
00:50:25,280 --> 00:50:28,440
Yes, we are!

559
00:50:28,520 --> 00:50:29,360
That's right.

560
00:50:29,440 --> 00:50:33,560
This year, everyone's gone
all out with their performances.

561
00:50:33,640 --> 00:50:37,400
Without further ado,

562
00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:39,840
please enjoy the performance from…

563
00:50:39,920 --> 00:50:44,440
- Peem and Sol from team PZX!
- Peem and Sol from team PZX!

564
00:50:52,600 --> 00:50:53,520
Damn.

565
00:50:53,600 --> 00:50:56,440
- Is that a team name or a motorbike model?
- Yeah.

566
00:50:56,520 --> 00:50:58,040
You guys are quite funny, you know?

567
00:50:58,120 --> 00:50:59,040
What?

568
00:53:23,320 --> 00:53:24,480
Qin.

569
00:53:24,560 --> 00:53:26,960
Get ready. And where's Duang?

570
00:53:27,040 --> 00:53:28,360
He went to the washroom.

571
00:53:28,440 --> 00:53:29,760
Okay, I'll give you the cue.

572
00:53:29,840 --> 00:53:30,840
Go.

573
00:54:35,640 --> 00:54:37,080
What are you doing?

574
00:54:39,240 --> 00:54:40,400
Getting my Qin energy.

575
00:55:23,320 --> 00:55:25,440
That was amazing!

576
00:55:25,520 --> 00:55:27,480
- Spectacular.
- You guys sang really well.

577
00:55:27,560 --> 00:55:29,400
You also danced really well.

578
00:55:29,480 --> 00:55:30,880
We have some questions for you.

579
00:55:30,960 --> 00:55:32,960
How does it feel
performing for this many people?

580
00:55:34,320 --> 00:55:37,200
It's very exciting.

581
00:55:38,520 --> 00:55:40,600
Both of you did marvelously.

582
00:55:40,680 --> 00:55:42,200
It was a great performance.

583
00:55:42,280 --> 00:55:46,680
- That's true.
- Another round of applause for them!

584
00:55:48,000 --> 00:55:49,840
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

585
00:55:55,520 --> 00:55:56,480
Damn.

586
00:55:56,560 --> 00:55:58,320
Peem is totally handsome!

587
00:55:58,400 --> 00:56:01,080
Is Duang going to make it
or will he be crushed to pieces?

588
00:56:01,160 --> 00:56:02,640
At this rate…

589
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:03,880
He'll make it?

590
00:56:03,960 --> 00:56:05,840
He's doomed. I'll put money on it.

591
00:56:05,920 --> 00:56:06,840
Qin's gonna carry him.

592
00:56:07,400 --> 00:56:09,800
Okay, everyone.
Here comes the next performance.

593
00:56:09,880 --> 00:56:11,400
Please give it up for

594
00:56:11,480 --> 00:56:15,880
Duang and Qin from the team
"Not The Best, But Still good!"

595
00:57:03,160 --> 00:57:05,880
<i>All the good things</i>

596
00:57:05,960 --> 00:57:07,640
- Sheesh!
- Damn!

597
00:57:07,720 --> 00:57:12,000
<i>I did it all 'cause</i>
<i>I've got you in my heart deep within</i>

598
00:57:12,080 --> 00:57:14,480
<i>If you're looking for someone in mind</i>

599
00:57:16,520 --> 00:57:20,840
<i>Who is always willing</i>
<i>To walk along the path</i>

600
00:57:20,920 --> 00:57:22,240
<i>Then hold my hand</i>

601
00:57:25,360 --> 00:57:29,640
<i>No matter how far it is, have no fear</i>
<i>'Cause I've got you by my side</i>

602
00:57:29,720 --> 00:57:31,040
<i>I want you to know</i>

603
00:57:34,320 --> 00:57:37,040
<i>I've got what you need in my arms</i>

604
00:57:37,120 --> 00:57:41,000
<i>Let me take care of you, keep you warm</i>

605
00:57:42,760 --> 00:57:46,440
<i>The emotion isn't coming through yet.</i>

606
00:57:51,480 --> 00:57:52,360
<i>Well…</i>

607
00:57:52,960 --> 00:57:55,520
I mean, the immersion…

608
00:57:55,600 --> 00:57:58,040
It feels like you're not that immersed.

609
00:57:58,120 --> 00:57:59,920
<i>Do you feel that way, Qin?</i>

610
00:58:02,880 --> 00:58:04,320
<i>Stop crying!</i>

611
00:58:04,400 --> 00:58:05,800
<i>Stop yelling!</i>

612
00:58:10,120 --> 00:58:11,400
<i>I told you to stop!</i>

613
00:58:30,200 --> 00:58:33,800
<i>No matter how far</i>

614
00:58:38,960 --> 00:58:43,120
<i>Or how long it takes</i>

615
00:58:44,320 --> 00:58:48,480
<i>I'll be there for you</i>

616
00:58:49,360 --> 00:58:53,440
<i>When you're all alone</i>

617
00:58:59,680 --> 00:59:03,440
<i>Every moment with you</i>

618
00:59:06,880 --> 00:59:11,880
<i>Is enough to fill my heart</i>

619
00:59:15,560 --> 00:59:20,560
<i>As we walk side by side</i>

620
00:59:25,240 --> 00:59:27,400
<i>It's nothing fancy</i>

621
00:59:29,680 --> 00:59:34,040
<i>What I've done was with my sincerity</i>

622
00:59:34,120 --> 00:59:35,840
<i>Doesn't matter what lies ahead</i>

623
00:59:35,920 --> 00:59:37,920
Those are my friends.

624
00:59:38,600 --> 00:59:42,880
<i>I did it all 'cause</i>
<i>I've got you in my heart deep within</i>

625
00:59:42,960 --> 00:59:44,320
<i>Hold my hand</i>

626
00:59:47,520 --> 00:59:52,040
<i>No matter how far it is, have no fear</i>
<i>'Cause I've got you by my side</i>

627
00:59:52,120 --> 00:59:53,360
<i>I want you to know</i>

628
00:59:56,320 --> 00:59:59,160
<i>I've got what you need in my arms</i>

629
00:59:59,240 --> 01:00:03,720
<i>Let me take care of you, keep you warm</i>

630
01:00:04,720 --> 01:00:06,680
<i>No matter how far</i>

631
01:00:06,760 --> 01:00:09,240
<i>Or how long it takes</i>

632
01:00:09,320 --> 01:00:11,160
<i>I'll be there for you</i>

633
01:00:11,240 --> 01:00:13,600
<i>When you're all alone</i>

634
01:00:13,680 --> 01:00:20,520
<i>Every moment with you</i>
<i>Is enough to fill my heart</i>

635
01:00:21,120 --> 01:00:25,200
<i>As we walk side by side</i>

636
01:00:34,960 --> 01:00:37,160
<i>I have a good chance</i>

637
01:00:37,760 --> 01:00:40,440
<i>To stay with you, to see your motion</i>

638
01:00:42,680 --> 01:00:44,600
<i>Tonight is too short</i>

639
01:00:45,240 --> 01:00:48,760
<i>Won't you stay a bit longer?</i>

640
01:00:48,840 --> 01:00:50,800
<i>Yeah, yeah, yeah</i>

641
01:00:50,920 --> 01:00:53,520
<i>Let me sing</i>

642
01:00:54,080 --> 01:00:56,240
<i>Just one song</i>

643
01:00:57,920 --> 01:01:01,440
<i>A song makes you</i>

644
01:01:01,520 --> 01:01:04,520
<i>Sleep for all night long</i>

645
01:01:05,600 --> 01:01:08,800
<i>Every moment with you</i>

646
01:01:10,120 --> 01:01:13,400
<i>Is more than enough to fill my heart</i>

647
01:01:13,480 --> 01:01:16,880
<i>As we walk</i>

648
01:01:17,400 --> 01:01:20,840
<i>Side by side</i>

649
01:04:25,120 --> 01:04:26,400
Amazing!

650
01:04:41,400 --> 01:04:43,800
Funan.

651
01:04:43,880 --> 01:04:46,240
You actually made it.

652
01:04:47,440 --> 01:04:49,720
I told you I'm too lazy to work.

653
01:04:50,280 --> 01:04:52,240
Did you get here in time
to see me onstage?

654
01:04:52,800 --> 01:04:54,800
You sounded like
you didn't want me to be here.

655
01:04:54,880 --> 01:04:57,000
But that doesn't seem to be the case.

656
01:04:57,720 --> 01:04:58,720
Right.

657
01:04:58,800 --> 01:05:00,640
Your partner on stage,

658
01:05:00,720 --> 01:05:02,960
he danced way better than you.

659
01:05:03,720 --> 01:05:06,720
It's true. How was I onstage?

660
01:05:07,280 --> 01:05:11,160
Gosh. Pretty good,
for someone who vanished on Mom.

661
01:05:12,520 --> 01:05:14,080
Was that a compliment or an insult?

662
01:05:14,160 --> 01:05:16,760
I feel like an ungrateful child.

663
01:05:16,840 --> 01:05:19,520
Right. I just sent the video.

664
01:05:20,680 --> 01:05:22,280
Mom and Dad should be calling us soon.

665
01:05:22,840 --> 01:05:23,960
In three,

666
01:05:24,800 --> 01:05:25,800
two,

667
01:05:26,560 --> 01:05:27,840
one…

668
01:05:27,920 --> 01:05:29,240
They're actually calling us.

669
01:05:32,240 --> 01:05:33,280
Hello, Dad?

670
01:05:33,800 --> 01:05:34,960
You finished watching?

671
01:05:35,040 --> 01:05:37,080
Yeah, we weren't doing anything.

672
01:05:37,160 --> 01:05:40,240
Mom made me watch it, so I had no choice.

673
01:05:40,320 --> 01:05:41,440
By the way,

674
01:05:41,520 --> 01:05:43,840
<i>Dad, Duang is right here.</i>
<i>Do you want to talk to him?</i>

675
01:05:43,920 --> 01:05:46,320
Turn on the speaker!
I can't hear them clearly.

676
01:05:47,880 --> 01:05:48,920
Hello, Duang?

677
01:05:49,000 --> 01:05:52,800
Hello, Mom? How did I do?

678
01:05:52,880 --> 01:05:55,480
Duang! You knocked it out of the park.

679
01:05:55,560 --> 01:05:57,600
You danced well,
and your moves were so tight.

680
01:05:57,680 --> 01:05:59,040
You blew it out of the water.

681
01:05:59,120 --> 01:06:01,280
You stood out the most. Do you know that?

682
01:06:01,360 --> 01:06:04,600
Come on, Mom! That's too much praise.

683
01:06:04,680 --> 01:06:06,480
<i>Come on, it's not.</i>

684
01:06:06,560 --> 01:06:09,560
We both agree, you know?
Come on, say that you do!

685
01:06:10,120 --> 01:06:12,120
Right!

686
01:06:12,200 --> 01:06:15,040
I almost mistook you
for a professional singer.

687
01:06:15,120 --> 01:06:16,240
What is it called?

688
01:06:16,320 --> 01:06:18,560
The term is "T-Pop," right?

689
01:06:19,600 --> 01:06:20,720
How do you know that?

690
01:06:20,800 --> 01:06:21,760
<i>Come on!</i>

691
01:06:21,840 --> 01:06:25,480
You barely put your effort into anything,
so I did some research.

692
01:06:25,560 --> 01:06:26,960
<i>I really wanted to be there,</i>

693
01:06:27,040 --> 01:06:28,280
but you didn't invite me.

694
01:06:28,360 --> 01:06:31,720
Or else both of us
would be there front and center.

695
01:06:31,800 --> 01:06:34,280
It's okay, Mom. You'd embarrass me.

696
01:06:34,360 --> 01:06:36,120
<i>This already delights me.</i>

697
01:06:36,640 --> 01:06:38,320
<i>Embarrass? How?</i>

698
01:06:38,400 --> 01:06:41,160
You're embarrassed by my love?
I'm upset!

699
01:06:41,920 --> 01:06:43,240
Mom, I'm sorry.

700
01:06:43,320 --> 01:06:46,280
Come on, Mom.
I've sent you all of the videos.

701
01:06:46,360 --> 01:06:47,920
<i>Stop being so grumpy.</i>

702
01:06:48,920 --> 01:06:51,240
Duang. The guys want to take a photo.

703
01:06:52,280 --> 01:06:54,560
Duang. Your friend's calling.

704
01:06:55,240 --> 01:06:57,200
Tell Dad we'll talk to him later at home.

705
01:06:58,480 --> 01:07:00,080
<i>We'll talk to you soon, Dad.</i>

706
01:07:00,160 --> 01:07:01,040
- Right.
- All right.

707
01:07:02,280 --> 01:07:03,320
Dad, play it.

708
01:07:03,400 --> 01:07:04,480
- The videos!
- Again?

709
01:07:04,560 --> 01:07:06,560
One more.
I want to study the choreography.

710
01:07:07,840 --> 01:07:10,120
- Are you sure?
- Get your hands ready.

711
01:07:10,200 --> 01:07:11,600
- It goes like this.
- Right.

712
01:07:13,880 --> 01:07:15,920
Funan, this is Qin.

713
01:07:17,000 --> 01:07:19,000
Qin, this is Funan.

714
01:07:19,080 --> 01:07:20,600
He's my older brother.

715
01:07:21,640 --> 01:07:23,520
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

716
01:07:24,560 --> 01:07:25,840
Go with your friends.

717
01:07:25,920 --> 01:07:27,480
I'm heading back to work now.

718
01:07:27,560 --> 01:07:28,560
Over there.

719
01:07:32,240 --> 01:07:35,520
Curse you, Funan!
You messed up my hair!

720
01:07:40,080 --> 01:07:42,240
Hey, can you fix my hair?

721
01:07:45,640 --> 01:07:48,800
It's okay. I'll fix it myself.

722
01:08:05,760 --> 01:08:06,800
You already look great.

723
01:08:09,240 --> 01:08:10,640
You've got a lovely family.

724
01:08:12,920 --> 01:08:16,319
Are you so flustered
that you changed the topic?

725
01:08:16,399 --> 01:08:17,319
Wait.

726
01:08:17,880 --> 01:08:19,319
Where did you get the bouquet?

727
01:08:22,640 --> 01:08:23,479
It's from my family.

728
01:08:24,359 --> 01:08:26,120
You've also got a lovely family.

729
01:08:27,600 --> 01:08:28,680
Not as lovely as yours.

730
01:08:33,720 --> 01:08:34,960
Come on. Group photo time.

731
01:08:57,279 --> 01:08:59,160
Today went just as expected.

732
01:09:00,439 --> 01:09:01,439
How well did we do?

733
01:09:03,479 --> 01:09:04,960
What do you think?

734
01:09:06,840 --> 01:09:08,359
You did a great job, Duang.

735
01:09:09,479 --> 01:09:12,560
Without your help,
things would've been bad.

736
01:09:20,080 --> 01:09:21,800
It's because I've got you.

737
01:09:24,279 --> 01:09:26,720
Everyone gets nervous
when they're on stage.

738
01:09:27,880 --> 01:09:28,880
It's only natural.

739
01:09:29,479 --> 01:09:32,840
Don't you think it's embarrassing?

740
01:09:33,399 --> 01:09:34,319
Hey.

741
01:09:35,640 --> 01:09:37,520
You only messed up a small part.

742
01:09:37,600 --> 01:09:41,520
When you became one with the stage,
you were on fire.

743
01:09:43,680 --> 01:09:45,479
I'm not that good.

744
01:09:49,160 --> 01:09:52,080
You're not really going to admit that
you're good at singing?

745
01:09:53,880 --> 01:09:57,160
I'm not the only one who says this.
Everyone else also says it.

746
01:09:57,880 --> 01:09:59,680
I think I could've done better.

747
01:10:04,680 --> 01:10:05,760
Well…

748
01:10:08,520 --> 01:10:10,240
I'll always have your back.

749
01:10:14,160 --> 01:10:15,040
Do you think about…

750
01:10:16,560 --> 01:10:18,240
between Peem's and our performance,

751
01:10:19,400 --> 01:10:21,480
which one the audience preferred?

752
01:10:24,480 --> 01:10:26,040
I never thought about that.

753
01:10:31,920 --> 01:10:33,200
<i>While I was performing,</i>

754
01:10:33,760 --> 01:10:36,320
<i>when I saw the audience enjoying it…</i>

755
01:10:38,480 --> 01:10:40,080
it really felt euphoric.

756
01:10:43,920 --> 01:10:44,920
Stunning, wasn't it?

757
01:10:49,680 --> 01:10:50,840
The ocean of light.

758
01:11:09,400 --> 01:11:10,400
What are you doing?

759
01:11:21,280 --> 01:11:23,600
QIN_ MENTIONED YOU IN HIS STORY

760
01:11:34,440 --> 01:11:35,960
You tagged me?

761
01:11:38,280 --> 01:11:39,800
This is the first time.

762
01:11:43,600 --> 01:11:44,520
And…

763
01:11:45,760 --> 01:11:47,840
Is there a meaning behind it?

764
01:11:48,400 --> 01:11:50,040
It's an important moment.

765
01:11:51,560 --> 01:11:53,240
So I want to treasure it while I can.

766
01:12:21,040 --> 01:12:22,240
Hey.

767
01:12:27,320 --> 01:12:28,720
You can't do this.

768
01:12:31,040 --> 01:12:32,200
Why not?

769
01:12:33,240 --> 01:12:34,120
Well…

770
01:12:36,760 --> 01:12:37,920
I'm flustered.

771
01:13:03,040 --> 01:13:04,600
Feeling better now?

772
01:13:08,800 --> 01:13:09,880
Just a little longer.

773
01:13:15,840 --> 01:13:17,280
You're such a tease.

774
01:13:19,520 --> 01:13:20,720
Be patient.

775
01:13:47,160 --> 01:13:48,600
Shall we take this more seriously?

776
01:13:59,440 --> 01:14:01,920
You said… What?

777
01:14:02,840 --> 01:14:03,800
Like…

778
01:14:06,600 --> 01:14:09,000
Let it be known
we're in the talking stage.

779
01:14:10,880 --> 01:14:11,960
Okay?

780
01:14:23,360 --> 01:14:24,440
That's great.

781
01:14:25,160 --> 01:14:26,200
That's excellent.

782
01:18:26,400 --> 01:18:27,320
Come on.

783
01:18:59,280 --> 01:19:00,520
How adorable.

784
01:19:00,600 --> 01:19:02,560
<i>I'm going to Bang Saen</i>
<i>to work on a art project.</i>

785
01:19:02,640 --> 01:19:03,520
<i>With?</i>

786
01:19:03,600 --> 01:19:04,480
Do they like you?

787
01:19:04,560 --> 01:19:05,840
Are you jealous?

788
01:19:07,360 --> 01:19:09,760
<i>You guys are joined at the hip.</i>
<i>What's your deal?</i>

789
01:19:09,840 --> 01:19:10,800
<i>It's getting serious.</i>

790
01:19:10,880 --> 01:19:12,800
Only just now? You took ages to.

791
01:19:12,880 --> 01:19:14,560
<i>Yes, Qin is everything to me.</i>

792
01:19:14,640 --> 01:19:15,480
<i>He's so handsome.</i>

793
01:19:15,560 --> 01:19:17,280
<i>No wonder you're this desperate.</i>

794
01:19:17,360 --> 01:19:18,640
<i>Nope, Qin's adorable.</i>

795
01:19:18,720 --> 01:19:20,080
He's only like that to you.

796
01:19:20,160 --> 01:19:22,720
Or are you just
head over heels in love with him, dumbass?

797
01:19:22,800 --> 01:19:23,760
Qin.
